      "content": "i hear you on the balance part, but you basically just said prioritizing secularism is \"essential.\" isn't that a bit of a stretch? some would argue that if you strip away religious exemptions, you're actually being less \"fair\" by ignoring a person's core identity. aren't you just saying that religious beliefs are secondary to state mandates?",
